      <section class="section story-grid">
        <div class="story-copy">
          <p class="section-label">Our ethos</p>
          <h2>Child-centred, trauma-informed, always</h2>
          <p>We are child-centred in everything we do. We listen first, ask thoughtful questions and build care around the individual, not a system.</p>
          <p>Our therapeutic approach is grounded in the PACE model, developed by Dr Daniel Hughes. PACE recognises that children who have experienced trauma need safety, connection and understanding before they can grow.</p>
          <p>We also embed restorative practice. When things go wrong, we focus on understanding, repair and learning, not punishment.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="pace-panel" data-pace-panel>
          <div class="pace-grid" role="tablist" aria-label="PACE model">
            <button class="pace-card is-active" type="button" role="tab" aria-selected="true" data-pace-tab data-title="Playfulness" data-letter="P" data-copy="Warmth, lightness and safe connection help children experience adults as approachable, steady and human." data-example="In practice: staff use gentle humour, shared activities and warm tone to lower anxiety without minimising feelings.">
              <span>P</span><strong>Playfulness</strong><small>Warmth and safe connection.</small>
            </button>
            <button class="pace-card" type="button" role="tab" aria-selected="false" data-pace-tab data-title="Acceptance" data-letter="A" data-copy="Acceptance separates the child from the behaviour, helping young people feel seen without shame." data-example="In practice: staff acknowledge feelings first, then work with the child to understand choices and repair harm.">
              <span>A</span><strong>Acceptance</strong><small>Seeing the child beyond behaviour.</small>
            </button>
            <button class="pace-card" type="button" role="tab" aria-selected="false" data-pace-tab data-title="Curiosity" data-letter="C" data-copy="Curiosity asks what sits underneath behaviour, rather than jumping straight to correction or consequence." data-example="In practice: staff ask thoughtful, non-judgemental questions and look for unmet needs, triggers and worries.">
              <span>C</span><strong>Curiosity</strong><small>Asking what sits underneath.</small>
            </button>
            <button class="pace-card" type="button" role="tab" aria-selected="false" data-pace-tab data-title="Empathy" data-letter="E" data-copy="Empathy meets difficult feelings with care, helping children feel understood before they are asked to move forward." data-example="In practice: staff name emotions, stay regulated and offer reassurance while boundaries remain clear.">
              <span>E</span><strong>Empathy</strong><small>Meeting feelings with care.</small>
            </button>
          </div>
          <article class="pace-detail" role="tabpanel" data-pace-detail>
            <span data-pace-letter>P</span>
            <div>
              <h3 data-pace-title>Playfulness</h3>
              <p data-pace-copy>Warmth, lightness and safe connection help children experience adults as approachable, steady and human.</p>
              <p data-pace-example>In practice: staff use gentle humour, shared activities and warm tone to lower anxiety without minimising feelings.</p>
            </div>
          </article>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="band blue">
        <div class="section">
          <p class="section-label">Values</p>
          <h2>What we stand for</h2>
          <div class="grid three">
            <article class="feature"><h3>Safety First</h3><p>Every decision begins with one question: is this child safe?</p></article>
            <article class="feature"><h3>Every Voice Matters</h3><p>Children participate in care plans, daily decisions and home meetings.</p></article>
            <article class="feature"><h3>Holistic Care</h3><p>We support the whole person: body, mind, relationships and future.</p></article>
            <article class="feature"><h3>Identity and Culture</h3><p>We celebrate diversity and support cultural, religious and personal identity.</p></article>
            <article class="feature"><h3>Transparency</h3><p>We communicate openly with families, authorities and professionals.</p></article>
            <article class="feature"><h3>Improvement</h3><p>Our team reflects, learns and evolves through supervision and training.</p></article>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="section" id="leadership">
        <p class="section-label">Leadership</p>
        <h2>Experienced, accountable and child-focused</h2>
        <p class="section-intro">Animate Care is led by experienced professionals with backgrounds in child protection, social work, residential childcare, safeguarding, regulation and quality assurance.</p>
        <div class="grid two">
          <article class="role staff-preview-card">
