      <section class="section">
        
        <h2>About Animate Care: questions answered</h2>
        <div class="faq-list">
          <details class="faq-item"><summary>Who runs Animate Care?</summary><p>Animate Care is led by Tapiwa Kunodro as Responsible Individual and Toni Berry as Registered Manager.</p></details>
          <details class="faq-item"><summary>What regulations does Animate Care follow?</summary><p>Animate Care operates under the Children's Homes (England) Regulations 2015, the Care Standards Act 2000 and the Children's Acts 1989 and 2004.</p></details>
          <details class="faq-item"><summary>What is the PACE model?</summary><p>PACE stands for Playfulness, Acceptance, Curiosity and Empathy. It underpins daily practice and helps children feel safe enough to engage.</p></details>
          <details class="faq-item"><summary>How does Animate Care involve children in their own care?</summary><p>Children participate in Placement Plans, regular meetings and daily decisions, supported by key workers who advocate for their views and needs.</p></details>
        </div>
